# MinGW support
- `python nvim.py` opens file, fix args forwarding
- Asynchronous querying of breakpoints and commands (no wait)
- handle <up arrow> in pywinpty PDB
- debug logging from gdb and lldb
- lldb support
- Press any key to exit: need to unblock msvcrt.getch() somehow
- cmake test in win32?
- Visual tests: attach('tcp', address=...)
- pty resizing with neovim

Store and load breakpoints between sessions
